k relative aspect-square h-8 w-8 lg:hidden inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/163786-82999c00-f8d3-457d-b592-e28f768759b7-profile.png?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-circle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="Imbion"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/Imbion" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="Imbion">Imbion</a><a href="https://cohost.org/Imbion" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->Imbion<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-03-29T16:04:48.704Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Fri, Mar 29, 2024, 4:04 PM"><a href="#comment-3c691629-ec60-44c9-b67b-9474b803bd6b" class="hover:underline">3/29/2024, 4:04 PM</a></time></div><div class="co-prose prose overflow-hidden break-words"><p>Discord is very cool for having an active community to keep up with and interact with, but it&#x27;s <!-- --><em>very<!-- --></em> bad for storing information that&#x27;s meant to be constantly accessed (like guides or information on a hobby).<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>Getting support on Discord is also very bad because questions could have already been asked several times over (but you can&#x27;t search for them easily), and it&#x27;s very common for your questions to get buried. Even then, because of the fast pace of a lot of larger discord servers, it&#x27;s very easy for any questions you are asking to get misunderstood and to have it confused for asking for something else, especially if you&#x27;re asking a question that&#x27;s more advanced than is typically seen in whatever channel you&#x27;re asking for help in.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>Also, most Discord servers get deleted eventually, and that just completely obliterates any and all information on them. This is why you can&#x27;t rely on them as a longterm vessel for information.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>This isn&#x27;t really Discord as an application&#x27;s fault. It&#x27;s not built for this level of information accessibility, because it is first and foremost an instant messaging app. However, as social media has dominated the modern internet and setting up a Discord server is very easy, a lot of people end up taking that option without even taking a second to consider something else.<!-- --></p></div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-2"><button class="co-link-button flex cursor-pointer flex-row 
